UNITED STATES of America, Plaintiff-Appellee, v. Luis Miguel Porto-Carredo ESTUPINAN, Defendant-Appellant. No. 05-16860

Non-Argument Calendar.

United States Court of Appeals, Eleventh Circuit. June 7, 2006. Luis Miguel Porto-Carredo Estupinan, Lisbon, OH, pro se. Yvette Rhodes Harrison, Tampa, FL, for Plaintiff-Appellee. Before CARNES, BARKETT and PRYOR, Circuit Judges. PER CURIAM:

Luis Miguel Porto-Carrero Estupinan, pro se, appeals the district court’s denial of his motion to correct an illegal sentence, pursuant to 18 U.S.C. §§ 3582(c), and/or 3742(a). Because Estupinan’s sentence was final when he filed his motion, the district court correctly determined that it lacked jurisdiction to entertain the motion.

AFFIRMED.
